# Input for the hash-pinned CI tooling lockfile.
#
# These are CI-only tools (linters + security scanners). They are NEVER
# bundled into the PyInstaller EXE, so this is separate from the runtime
# lock (requirements/lock.txt, compiled from pyproject.toml).
#
# Pinning + hashing them satisfies OpenSSF Scorecard Pinned-Dependencies and
# stops a compromised tool release from tampering with CI.
#
# Regenerate the lock after editing this file. Run it on Linux with
# Python 3.11 — that is exactly what every CI tooling job uses
# (ubuntu-latest + actions/setup-python python-version: '3.11'). Compiling
# on a newer Python drops version-conditional transitives (e.g.
# typing-extensions, only required by cyclonedx-python-lib on
# python_version < "3.13"), which then fail --require-hashes on 3.11:
#
#   python3.11 -m pip install pip-tools
#   python3.11 -m piptools compile --generate-hashes \
#       --output-file=requirements/ci-tools.txt requirements/ci-tools.in
#
# Renovate's lock-file maintenance keeps requirements/ci-tools.txt current the
# same way it does requirements/lock.txt.

pip
ruff
black
pip-audit
zizmor
